                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iv #iir" facs="002">Fols. iv, iir</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1002Annunciation">Annunciation</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiv" facs="003">Fol. iiv</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1092SacrificeIsaac">The Sacrifice of Isaac</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#8v" facs="012">Fol. 8v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref>, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#9r" facs="012">Fol. 9r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/>, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#24v" facs="028">Fol. 24v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1065RoadtoCalvary">Road to Calvary</ref>, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#25r" facs="028">Fol. 25r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref>, holding a book. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> and a male figure sit beside him, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#93v" facs="097">Fol. 93v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#115v" facs="119">Fol. 115v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#116r" facs="119">Fol. 116r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref>, before the cross</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d10">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#5v #27v #37r #86r #88v #91r #95r #96v #101r #104r" facs="009 031 040 089 092 094 098 100 104 107">folss. 5v, 27v, 37r, 86r, 88v, 91r, 95r, 96v, 101r, 104r, </locus>, multiple full stops;
                      <locus target="#76v #77r" facs="079">76v, 77r</locus>, line of alternating red and black dots</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#inside cover" facs="001">Fols. inside, </locus>Sticker on inside front cover includes the Tourism Sticker CV-A-3.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#ir #116v #117r #117v" facs="001 120 121">Fols. ir, 116v, 117r, 117v</locus>Blank</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc>The prayers include the names of departed people written in red ink.
                        For example,
                        Wäldä Gäbrǝʾel (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡</foreign>) appears on <locus target="#2v" facs="006">fol. 2v</locus>
                        Gäbrä Kidan (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ኪዳን፡</foreign>) appears on <locus target="#4r" facs="007">fol. 4r</locus>
                        Wälättä Śǝlasse (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>) appears on <locus target="#4r" facs="007">fol. 4r</locus></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc>The owner, the bishops, and the king are referred to as <foreign xml:lang="gez">እገሌ፡</foreign> ʿso-and-soʾ (e.g., <locus target="#71r #71v" facs="074 075">fols. 71r, 71v</locus>)</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Navigation system:
                        <locus target="#3 #38 #42" facs="006 041 045">folss. 3, 38, 42, </locus>, black string sewn into the fore edge;
                        <locus target="#76 #91" facs="079 094">76, 91, </locus>, red string sewn into the fore edge;
                        <locus target="#98" facs="101">98</locus>, yellow string sewn into top edge</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                        <desc>Scribal intervention:
                          words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#2v #3v #7v #10r #12v" facs="006 007 011 013 016">folss. 2v, 3v, 7v, 10r, 12v, </locus>, etc.;
                          and in the upper margin with a symbol (═) marking the location where the text is to be inserted <locus target="#11r #34v #61v #69r" facs="014 038 065 072">11r, 34v, 61v, 69r, </locus>;
                          erasure markings are visible <locus target="#7v" facs="011">7v, </locus>;
                          text has been removed <locus target="#4v #8r #33r #45v #46v" facs="008 011 036 049 050">4v, 8r, 33r, 45v, 46v</locus>, etc.</desc>
                        </item>
                      </list>
                    </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
